i got a hair cut today by erin again, i always enjoy getting haircuts even though i always think i look retarded in eric's bathroom mirror.

attempted to swim this morning but spent most of my time learning how to use a pool vaccuum and dodging praying mantises (mantees?  manti?) that land on pool nets.

it is a lot earlier than normal, for i am off to my first day of band camp.  the morning part won't be bad because it's just a dance team practice, but when i go back today at 3:30 with the entire band it's going to be hell.  

t-shirt tans + really weird band kids + heat + sunburn + general uncomfortableness = this week.

Maybe I can lose this belly of pudge I have gained ever since the cruise.

this summer has been going by very fast.  i haven't really accomplished much like i planned on doing, but that's how it is every year.

i'm going to my dad's for two weeks tomorrow and we're going to florida to visit my grandpa and on a Carnival cruise to the bahamas for 3 nights.  fun fun fun.


i'm going to come back to augusta just in time for band camp (woo) and...drumroll....I WILL HAVE A TAN.  i know this is something you may have to read twice as i am the queen of pale skin.  but contrary to popular belief, i do tan.  when i want to.  which doesn't really happen often.



anyways, i'm finished with all of my summer work for AP lit but i have yet to start on any of my large pictures for AP art.  they're so intimidating.  i don't know where to begin.



sleepy.

i am going to six flags tomorrow with eric, erin and ben for eric's 19th birthday, it's going to be supercool awesome fun.  

i have to figure out what im bringing...and pack lunches...and things.

the last time i went to six flags was the year the georgia scorcher opened..5 years ago or something?  woooooooo this will be super fun.

the end
The results are in! SAT Reasoning june 4th, 2005 Reading: 580 Math: 640 Writing: 630 (8 on the essay) Total: 1850 score. i'm happy. :)
no one kiss me for 24-48 hours, i have strep throat.

so i went to see bright eyes and the faint last night, here's my story. it all began with a drive to atlanta with sierra, cameron, and sierra's dad as our chauffer. Halfway there, i jokingly asked sierra if she had our tickets and her mouth dropped. She had never printed them out..! So we drove to her aunt's house in little five points to print them from her email. (end conundrum number one). Our friends Caroline and Jessica had gotten at the venue at 5, so we jumped in line with them. this allowed for us to be very close to the front. So when we went in, i headed straight for the front of the stage, where i saved myself a spot in 1st/2nd row depending on who was pushing me later. Surprisingly, no one in my group wanted to stand up with me and they all went and sat down in the seats in the back. But I toughed it out and stood up for 6 hours during the show. There were a lot of people smoking and i almost died. (end conundrum 2). The opening act was a rapper that had his bass up too loud. I felt like my eardrum was going to pop and that my ear was bleeding. I was very glad when he finished his set. (end conundrum number 3.) But then the Faint came on. I like the Faint but I have never been a ridiculously huge fan, but their live show was great. The lights made it awesome. The guitarist was hott.. ...And they even had a violinist! But then Bright Eyes came on. I must say I'm quite a fan, but i became a huge obnoxious fan x25894354895 when conor finally started playing. i guess seeing things live just kind of brings the music closer to you or something. It also helped that I was uber close to the stage. Conor is a lovely keyboardist... ...but he also rocks at guitar as well. But he does well without an instrument. (what an alcoholic.) The best part of it though was how conor jumped on top of everything. i failed to get a picture of him standing on top of his keyboard, but i did catch him dancing on the bass drum. Another super surprise was how Nick, the guitarist for the yeah yeah yeahs, played guitar for conor during the tour. mmmm. aaaaand i managed to walk home with a setlist from the stage. Good souvenir. Yes sir.

i went to a bellydancing class today.

it was pretty effing awesome.



the end.

i've got a whole summer ahead of me but i'm still stressing out that i won't finish all the stuff i have to do for ap art. if you see me at all, good luck finding me without my new awesome black sketchbook in my hands. i wish i could draw better than i do. i wish i was less sketchy with my lines and more precise. aaaand i wish i wasn't a procrastinator. on a happier note, i am almost 5/6 of the way through Jane Eyre for ap lit. it is the longest novel we have to read this summer so hopefully i can get all the lit readings out of the way quickly. on an even happier note, my headbands match my shirt perfectly and i'm going to a Pete and Pete party today to watch the entire first season on dvd.

photo entry of the ghs prom night. wo0t. well the day got off to a somewhat slow start. getting ready and things while my mother took pictures. ben arrived at my house soon after however, and we began to work on making our fake flower corsage/boutonneires. they were lovely by the way. naturally the mother had to take that priceless outdoor picture of the couple dressed in prom attire...though she wasn't too thrilled about our foot gear. then we were off to mcdonalds! ben was thrilled to meet mister ronald mcdonald himself. after enjoying a nice mcchicken sandwich, we headed over to abbis for a nice cup of coffee and a relaxing game of scrabble. mmm, vanilla lattes. after i beat him at scrabble, we had fun with letters. however it was getting kind of late and we had to meet our friends alex and emily at serendipity. so off we went with the sunset behind us. once we arrived at serendipity, alex and ben had to stake out the place to make sure it was safe. naturally it was so we enjoyed our milkshakes and took our group footwear photo. "it's getting late!" the men stated. prom had just begun downtown so we followed alex and emily to sacred heart. it was a beautiful view on the ride there. once we arrived at sacred heart, i met up with my girls outside and the men discussed men things. but it was getting boring so we headed inside for our prom. and boy was there a party inside. people were getting crunk right and left. but one can only do so much dancing so a few hours later, the posse headed over to d.timms for some late night entertainment. we were so enthused by the king of swing and rick james himself. then we got kind of hungry and decided to eat some cake. with full bellies and $11.77 less money in our wallets, we all parted ways. amy and jessica went home while alex and emily went somewhere and me and ben went off in the opposite direction. no pictures of what happened then. but it was an eventful evening from singing "time after time" with the jazz band at d.timms to eating chocolate covered strawberries at prom to reading all the reasons why you should say NO to sex while holding up a condom. and everything in between.

yeah so the state audition for ghp was today in atlanta...i got all dressed up in my business suit and matching accessories and uncomfortable shoes and did my interview.

i was really rambly though because the interviewers came up to me a little bit earlier than expected, so they caught me off guard.  ever since i shook their hands i was like iorjbg;sohtijtosniuj and i just kept talking, i'm not sure if it made sense or not.  i hope i didn't sound like an idiot.  and i messed with my hair a lot more than i probably should have.

i think they liked my stuff but i dont know if they think im GHP material or not, like the more i think about it the more i don't think i got in.  just because i forgot to say so much stuff i was going to say, like the interview went by so fast and it all just went over my head and i completely forgot all my main points until like 3 hours later.

but then i took the test which was uber easy so that was good, then i went and did some Atlanta shopping with my dad to get my mind off it. which was nice.

they're only taking 45 people out of 200, why must i have to wait till april to see who got in??

paris hilton was the host on snl tonight, sucks

i'm sick

GHP in 3 days

so i discovered today something i've always known but i just never followed.  it's not good to judge people.  and its not good to hate people for something if you don't know their whole story.  

it'll never help the situation and just makes you bitter and senile and unlikable.  

i'm probably going to forget this in a few days but hopefully typing it out will help me remember.  cause it's a great thing to keep in mind.










(and shoutout to my secret teller rachel, holla back)

i love my life.  i love my friends.  my new years resolution is to never take for granted what i have ever again.

no matter what i want to happen, it doesn't matter.  because i still have so much around me that i've been overlooking for a long time.

i'm sorry to everyone that has been in that shadow.  i'm sorry to myself for ever thinking that what i wanted would be better than what i have.

i love you all.  happy new year!

I've been laying in bed for the last hour unable to fall back asleep. I hate it. And I've been singing that damn Alanis Morisette song "You Oughta Know" in my head the whole time. I hate how life is a struggle. Once you get past one thing, you get faced with another. It never ends. Sometimes it's too hard to make the good times outweigh the bad. January 3rd, 2005--I've got to start a new life without you and I'm really scared. For the past two years I've been able to talk to you about anything and now I've got to pretend you don't even exist. All for what? I don't know. I can already see it coming back to haunt me. But at the same time, this has got to end. This jealousy of something that has nothing to do with anything has got to end. But is it really possible to get rid of something so prevalent in human nature? I've got so many doubts. And I think they outweigh the possible positive outcomes right now. Yet I've never needed something so bad for me. I think I'm being dramatic. But I also think that a friendship that has grown into an unconditional love gone out of control can't just be thrown away either. I even begin to think that this is just one of those larger bumps in that unpaved road of life and there are more even larger than this up ahead. But that doesn't change the fact that this bump is large to begin with. I know most won't read this entire entry. It won't make sense to them. But it makes sense to me. Yet somehow I feel like the most confused person on the face of the earth. So please back away and let me go I can't my darling, I love you so... edit: p.s. merry christmas everybody.

ssooooo...christmas break. i've had better. i left on friday to come to my dad's house then saturday we drove to florida to visit the family. my grandma is really sick. i don't really know how much longer she has left and i can tell she is really wearing out my grandpa. i didn't really know how to act so i just sat there quiet most of the trip. we got back yesterday and i am still at my dad's house...whenever i come here i always feel so antisocial and lonely. i hate it. i wish he lived closer to augusta so i could still hang out with people i love...yet i hate saying that because this is supposed to be a time when i hang out with my dad. but this is the time in my life where i don't want to hang out with my parents. bah i hate being so jealous

whether it's the best of times
or the worst of times

..it's the only time we've got

brand new day.  and i've got on my tights.  and i woke up this morning with not a single curl frizzed up on my head so it's got to be a sign.

good day?
